{"key":"post-10427992","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10427992</id>\n<content>If the grains are coming out too dry, you're probably failing to reduce the stove setting once pressure is reached.&amp;nbsp; Every time the weight rattles, moisture is lost from your jars.&amp;nbsp; I usually reduce heat so the PC runs at 14 psi, and the weight doesn't rattle at all.&amp;nbsp; Make sure you're letting it vent steam with the weight off for several minutes at the start of each cycle before building pressure.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10428009</next>\n<prev>10427986</prev>\n<first>10427947</first>\n<last>10435113</last>\n<when>1243751997</when>\n<utime>05/31/09 09:39 AM</utime>\n</post>"}